post_text:
Parents/Guardians/Students,
Please be aware that with the upcoming school year :Not only are vaccinations still required for school attendance it is even more important than ever to stay current to avoid outbreaks of other preventable communicable illnesses when we are battling Covid. We still have to exclude students who are not up to date on required immunizations - with proof on file - after the first 14 days of school. Please make an appointment with your PCP or at Whitney Young Health.

We are bridging technological gaps for our students to ensure that all students have access to devices and are able to work uninterrupted on all of their school assignments. Accepting this device means that my child is fully responsible for completing all his work online as assigned to him by Green Tech High. If I do not accept this device, it means that I have a device and my child is also fully responsible for completing all work assigned by Green Tech High Charter School.

Please see the important pickup instructions below. You must arrive at the designated entrance and time according to your scholar’s last name and grade level. If there is a line, please remember to stay 6 feet apart for social distancing purposes. Parents will need to sign 2 copies of the chrome book contracts. Each station will be equipped with hand sanitizer and Clorox/Lysol wipes. Staff will be wearing masks and gloves during the distribution process. Pens will be wiped down after each visitor as a precautionary measure. Please review the pickup information below:

post_text:
Yesterday, the Green Tech Track team made school history as the first team to qualify for the State Meet. The 4x200 relay team made a huge upset yesterday at the State Qualifier Meet at UAlbany coming from a 5th place ranking in the prelims to taking 2nd overall and qualifying for States. The 4x200 relay team comprised of Kyrston Drew, Andriew Garcia, Chris Barry Jr., and Majid Musa. These young men will represent Green Tech and Section 2 at the NYS Indoor Track and Field State Meet hosted by Ocean Breeze in Staten Island. If you see any of these young men today please congratulate them on this major accomplishment.

Thanks for all your support of these young men as students and athletes.
